values:
She's a maaaaaaneater, make you work hard, make you-

...

Oh Christ. I really am losing it. Which I kind of sort of completely blame on the little cage that work and school have boxed me into. 
Though my profs have been dropping ten pound hints that they're considering debating hours with some of the public employers,so school work is, most likely, going to be a bit less consuming.

I mean, I'd kill for a bit of free time.

...make you buy cars, make you cut cards wish you never ever OH GOD DAMN IT.

I'm not even gonna ask how my email got distributed so widely but...uh... looking at my inbox today I wonder why I even have, use, or check it. 

There are apparently 225 girls, 83 guys and about 14 whose genders were unintelligible via email, wandering around Domino waiting to do things I will not repeat involving my manhood. Be very afraid.

Wow. Tomorrow will be reeeeal exciting.

Why do the SCARY ones always hit on ME?

I wonder if I could fake something unfornate convincingly and get my homework off of someone from study group. Or claim there's some emergency down at the company that needs handling.

Well, if enough annoying kids from class send badly written flirty emails it might bug up a server...

All these love-devoted days kinda remind me of communism. It has good principles, works in theory, and the minute it's put into practice it all falls apart because people get distracted by the idea of making a profit over genuine emotion of the masses. Not that I'm one to talk but still.
